<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1399,682,814]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,421,682,708]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,421,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Cheilosia flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[430,523,683,709]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is described from a single female specimen. As the male sex of the new species remains unknown, a subgeneric placement of the new taxon is not proposed. Characteristics like yellow parafacia, eye short pilose, separated antennal pits and brown colour of body separates 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1260,1398,752,779]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1260,1398,752,779]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,280,788,814]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all other known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[785,897,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[785,897,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Cheilosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See also under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1091,1189,788,814]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versa">
<emphasis box="[1091,1189,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">C. versa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption pageId="44" pageNumber="45" startId="44.[189,232,1964,1990]" targetBox="[353,1243,973,1887]" targetPageId="44">
