</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[189,1180,311,338]" box="[189,1180,311,338]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[436,544,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena">
<emphasis box="[436,544,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is from Latin and refers to the yellow colour of gena.
</paragraph>
